                            <comment id="13056792" author="mgarski" created="Tue, 28 Jun 2011 21:17:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching two files - one for the unit test (TestFunctionQuery.patch) and one for the fix (FileFloatSource.patch).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue can be reproduced using the patch for the test, which creates a multi-segment index.  Applying the FileFloatSource.patch will correct the issue and allow the test to pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13056807" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 28 Jun 2011 21:42:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Michael, it looks like this bug was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2831&quot; title=&quot;Revise Weight#scorer &amp;amp; Filter#getDocIdSet API to pass Readers context&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUCENE-2831&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-2831&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (hence this bug only existed in trunk).&lt;br/&gt;
I just committed the fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
